    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v46-cohort",
      "strategy_id": "v46-cohort",
      "cohort_label": "v46",
      "hypothesis": "v46 cohort - first live test of the regime entry gate. Adds regimeGate to 5 shadow mirrors of proven base strategies (v25, acc-gate, v44-climb, v44-1s-ttp10). The regime classifier (universe-level pump_rate / fast_rug_rate over the last 50 grads) is computed independently by /regime-analysis and exposed to the trade-evaluator as a cheap cached snapshot. Prior 14-day overlay data showed RED hours net -0.0014 SOL/trade across 230 live trades, vs YELLOW +0.0014/trade across 90 trades, vs GREEN +0.0005/trade on 71 trades after threshold recalibration - a monotone-correct ordering. Goal: validate that gating live entries against this signal improves outlier-robust net SOL accumulation vs the un-gated control. Four variants use skip_red (block RED only, allow YELLOW + GREEN); one variant (v46-v25-green-only) uses green_only as the more restrictive A/B. Sample-size caveat: at ~60% RED time-in-regime, the gated strategies will see ~40% of the trade volume of the un-gated control. Need n>=80 to evaluate drop3 vs base.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 0,
        "target_n": 100,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "cohort-level - see individual variants"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v46-v25-skip-red",
      "strategy_id": "v46-v25-skip-red",
      "cohort_label": "v46",
      "hypothesis": "Mainline regime-gate test. Mirror of v25-bot-excl-climbing (ON-TRACK, n=450, drop3 +5.94) with regimeGate=skip_red - skips entries when current regime is RED, allows GREEN + YELLOW. Hypothesis: cuts RED-hour entries (which run -0.0014 SOL/trade on the un-gated control) without sacrificing the YELLOW+GREEN winners. Expected volume: ~40% of v25 (since RED is ~60% of recent time). If per-trade mean rises meaningfully AND drop3 stays positive at n>=100, the gate is value-additive. Compare directly to v46-v25-green-only (the more restrictive A/B) to see whether YELLOW hours are worth keeping.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 1.5,
        "target_sol_per_mo": 7,
        "target_drop_top3": 0.5,
        "target_n": 100,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "n>=60 and net_sol<-1"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
